The paper discusses program synthesis and visualization techniques for automatically generating feedback for programming assignments, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and computer engineering (cs.CE). The focus on designing pedagogically useful hints and analyzing teachers' hint-giving practices suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) component. The use of visualization techniques and comparison of code execution traces suggests a natural language processing (cs.CL) component. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for program synthesis and feedback generation suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) component.
